# =============================================================================
# Dynamic Media Card Tool — Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
#
# This app uses ONLY X (Twitter) OAuth 2.0 for sign-in.
# There are no other sign-in methods. Clicking "Sign in with X" takes you
# straight to X's authorization page.
#
# =============================================================================
# 1. X_CLIENT_ID and X_CLIENT_SECRET (required)
# =============================================================================
# How to get them:
#   1. Go to https://developer.x.com (log in with the X account that will manage the app)
#   2. Create a new Project (or use an existing one)
#   3. Inside the Project, create a new App (or use existing)
#   4. In the App settings:
#        - Go to "User authentication settings"
#        - Enable OAuth 2.0
#        - App permissions: at minimum "Read and Write" (or Read if you only fetch)
#        - App type: "Web App, Automated App or Bot"
#        - Callback URI(s) / Redirect URI(s):
#            For local development: http://127.0.0.1:8000/callback
#            For production (Render etc.): https://your-app.onrender.com/callback
#          IMPORTANT: The value here must EXACTLY match X_REDIRECT_URI below (including http vs https and no trailing slash).
#   5. After saving, copy:
#        - Client ID     → X_CLIENT_ID
#        - Client Secret → X_CLIENT_SECRET  (shown only once — save it immediately)
#
# The app requests these scopes (hard-coded): tweet.read users.read offline.access
#
# =============================================================================
# 2. X_REDIRECT_URI (required)
# =============================================================================
# Must exactly match what you registered in the X App's OAuth 2.0 settings.
# Local example:
X_REDIRECT_URI=http://127.0.0.1:8000/callback
#
# Production example (change to your real deployed URL):
# X_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-dynamic-media-card-tool.onrender.com/callback

X_CLIENT_ID=your-x-client-id-here
X_CLIENT_SECRET=your-x-client-secret-here

# =============================================================================
# 3. SECRET_KEY (required for sessions + token encryption)
# =============================================================================
# Generate a strong random value. Never commit the real one.
# Good ways to generate:
#   - macOS / Linux:   openssl rand -hex 32
#   - Python:          python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
#
# For local testing you can use a long dummy, but change it before any real use.
SECRET_KEY=replace-with-a-long-random-string-at-least-32-characters

# =============================================================================
# 4. (Optional) OAUTHLIB_INSECURE_TRANSPORT
# =============================================================================
# Only for local development over plain http://127.0.0.1
# Leave commented out in production (https is required for real OAuth).
# OAUTHLIB_INSECURE_TRANSPORT=1

# =============================================================================
# Notes for Render / other deploys
# =============================================================================
# - Use the exact same variables above.
# - Set X_REDIRECT_URI to your production callback URL (https://.../callback)
# - The app has no database — schedules and tokens are in-memory only.
#   They disappear when the service restarts (normal on free Render).
# - Make sure your X App/Project has the "Ads API" product enabled,
#   otherwise the Ads account and card endpoints will return 403.
